<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000059#     1#        502.4#">Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.4</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_59.1-502.4"/><heading><desig>§ 59.1-502.4.</desig><title>Acceptance with varying terms</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>(a)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> In this section, an acceptance materially alters an offer if it contains a term that materially conflicts with or varies a term of the offer or that adds a material term not contained in the offer.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>(b)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Except as otherwise provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-502.5"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.5">§ 59.1-502.5<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#        502.5#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, a definite and seasonable expression of acceptance operates as an acceptance, even if the acceptance contains terms that vary from the terms of the offer, unless the acceptance materially alters the offer.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>(c)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If an acceptance materially alters the offer, the following rules apply:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c_1"/><heading><desig>(1)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A contract is not formed unless (A) a party agrees, such as by manifesting assent, to the other party's offer or acceptance or (B) all the other circumstances, including the conduct of the parties, establish a contract.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c_2"/><heading><desig>(2)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If a contract is formed by the conduct of both parties, the terms of the contract are determined under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-502.10"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.10">§ 59.1-502.10.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#       502.10#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText></level></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d"/><heading><desig>(d)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If an acceptance varies from but does not materially alter the offer, a contract is formed based on the terms of the offer. In addition, the following rules apply:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d_1"/><heading><desig>(1)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Terms in the acceptance which conflict with terms in the offer are not part of the contract.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d_2"/><heading><desig>(2)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> An additional nonmaterial term in the acceptance is a proposal for an additional term. Between merchants, the proposed additional term becomes part of the contract unless the offeror gives notice of objection before, or within a reasonable time after, it receives the proposed terms.</p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 101"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 101">2000, cc. 101<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2000#000101#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 996"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 996">996<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2000#000996#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PV50-004G-K4PM-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 59.1.</desig><title>TRADE AND COMMERCE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 43.</desig><title>UNIFORM COMPUTER INFORMATION TRANSACTIONS ACT</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="part"><heading><desig>PART 2.</desig><title>FORMATION AND TERMS</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Contracts Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QzY0RTZFMzE0RjkwNDdFQUI5M0U5N0ZFMjYyREMyQzU7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QTRDOTRGN0JCNjNBNDU3Mjg5MjVCM0QwQzgxRjkzRDk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QUI2NjI4OTk0QUM0NDlDMEIwMDFFNUQxNzEwMDhENkM</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RTAzNUFDNDBBMjdBNDgxOUEwNzRCNjdDN0Q3QzIyMTI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NjFDQjcyRDA0RDVDNDQ5MjlBMkQyRjAxRDEyQ0NEREM</classCode></classificationItem></classifi